<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-05T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-05T19:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/1172: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom (<persName type="to">Winant</persName>)</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-05T19:00:00-05:00">January 5,
                                    1942—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>44. Please expedite reply to Department’s no. 5630, December 3, 11 p.m.
                            Specific information would be helpful regarding the alleged payment by
                            the Greek Government for Australian wheat shipped as far as Egypt and
                            held there by the British Government. Rumors regarding such wheat
                            continue to circulate in Greece, and Axis propaganda has not failed to
                            take advantage of them.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>